    "And he spake also a parable unto them; <span class=\"word\">No man putteth a piece of a new garment upon an old; if otherwise, then both the new maketh a rent, and the piece that was taken out of the new agreeth not with the old.</span>",
    "<span class=\"word\">And no man putteth new wine into old bottles; else the new wine will burst the bottles, and be spilled, and the bottles shall perish.</span>",
    "<span class=\"word\">But new wine must be put into new bottles; and both are preserved.</span>",
    "<span class=\"word\">No man also having drunk old wine straightway desireth new: for he saith, The old is better.</span>",
