    "Now when the Pharisee which had bidden him saw it, he spake within himself, saying, This man, if he were a prophet, would have known who and what manner of woman this is that toucheth him: for she is a sinner.",
    "And <span class=\"person\">Jesus</span> answering said unto him, <span class=\"word\"><span class=\"person\">Simon</span>, I have somewhat to say unto thee.</span> And he saith, Master, say on.",
    "<span class=\"word\">There was a certain creditor which had two debtors: the one owed five hundred pence, and the other fifty.</span>",
    "<span class=\"word\">And when they had nothing to pay, he frankly forgave them both. Tell me therefore, which of them will love him most?</span>",
